TY  - JOUR
T1  - On Estimating Skewness in Stock Returns
AU  - Lau, Hon-Shiang
AU  - Wingender, John R.
AU  - Lau, Amy Hing-Ling
Y1  - 1989/09/01
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.35.9.1139
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.35.9.1139
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1139
EP  - 1142
VL  - 35
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In recent years skewness has become a much-discussed factor in financial research, and many studies/models involve the skewness of various financial variables. This paper (i) points out the universal neglect in the finance literature of skewness' sampling error and its significant consequences; (ii) presents a simple approach for roughly constructing a confidence interval for skewness estimated from lognormal populations; (iii) points out directions of further research for developing a comprehensive approach for estimating skewness reliably.
